                  <provenance>The original name of the donor has been washed out and replaced by the name of Takla Hāymānot, written in a secondary hand with a thin pen
                     (the same hand as that of <ref target="#a1"/>): <locus target="#2ra #4va #5va #16rb #39vb #47va #49va #52ra #57rb #62rb #78va #88ra #95rb #96rb #109rb #113va #233rb"/>.
                     Other names are written interlinearly in a different (more recent?) hand, in strong vermilion ink: Gabra Giyorgis (<locus target="#2ra #3rb #4va #5va #9ra #9va #233rb"/>), 
                     Takla ʾƎgziʾ (<locus target="#13ra #16rb"/>), Walatta ʿĀbiya ʾƎgziʾ (<locus target="#21ra"/>), Wal<add resp="IR">da</add> Śǝllāse (<locus target="#26vb"/>), 
                     Gabra Mikāʾel (<locus target="#35va"/>),  Walda Gabrʾel (<locus target="#39vb"/>), Walatta Gabrǝʾel (<locus target="#47va"/>), Walatta Śǝllāse (<locus target="#53vb"/>), 
                     ʿAmda Māryām (<locus target="#57rb"/>), Walatta ʾIyasus (<locus target="#78va"/>), Zamada Māryām (<locus target="#95rb"/>), Gabra Masqal (<locus target="#109rb"/>), 
                     ʾAqba Mikāʾel (<locus target="#155ra"/>), Fǝqǝrta Mikāʾel (<locus target="#233rb"/>).</provenance></history>
